<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1737,1950]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1737,1764]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Body form short and stout. Face slightly longer than wide, frontoclypeus expanded apically, lora small. Pronotum distinctly declivous, weakly arched, striations oblique. Forewing with 
<number box="[1174,1188,1775,1801]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
or 
<number box="[1227,1242,1775,1801]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
anteapical cells, veins spotted with white. 
<collectingCountry box="[451,510,1812,1838]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Hind</collectingCountry>
femoral spinulation 
<number box="[752,769,1812,1838]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[787,798,1812,1838]" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
. Male pygofer elongate with tiny apical spine or acute tip or caudal margin serrate, dorsal connectives variously armed, articulating against upper margins of pygophore. Aedeagal shaft curved near apex with or without pair of slender processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
